loading packages

library(tidyverse)
library(leaflet)
library(viridis) # nice color palette
library(sf) # newer "simple features" spatial package
library(tmap) # static mapping
library(USAboundaries) # data for USA boundaries
library(stringr)
library(data.table)
library(arrow)

reading in major and SM-80 facilities

maj_fac <- read_csv('/projects/caa-ml/raw_data/icis/icis-air_facilities.csv') %>% 
  filter(AIR_POLLUTANT_CLASS_CODE == "MAJ", STATE != 'TX') %>% 
  mutate(FAC_TYPE = 'MAJ') %>% 
  select(REGISTRY_ID, FACILITY_NAME, FAC_TYPE, CITY, COUNTY_NAME, STATE, ZIP_CODE, STREET_ADDRESS)
sm_80 <- read_csv('/projects/caa-ml/raw_data/icis/data_pull/sm80s.csv') %>% 
  filter(STATE_CODE != 'TX') %>% 
  rename(STREET_ADDRESS = LOCATION_ADDRESS,
         STATE = STATE_CODE,
         COUNTY_NAME = AIR_COUNTY,
         ZIP_CODE = ZIP) %>% 
  mutate(FAC_TYPE = 'SM') %>% 
  select(REGISTRY_ID, FACILITY_NAME, FAC_TYPE, CITY, COUNTY_NAME, STATE, ZIP_CODE,
         STREET_ADDRESS)

combining the two dataframes

fac_univ <- bind_rows(maj_fac, sm_80)

# appending additional location data to the address (remove street address entries
# with NA or co-ordinates or PORTABLE or Undetermined)
fac_univ$STREET_ADDRESS <- str_c(fac_univ$STREET_ADDRESS, ', ', fac_univ$COUNTY_NAME,
                                 ', ', fac_univ$CITY, ', ', fac_univ$STATE)

reading in facility co-ordinates dataset

fac_loc <- fread('/projects/caa-ml/raw_data/facility_locations.csv')

merging facility info with facility location

fac_merged <- fac_univ %>%
  left_join(fac_loc %>% 
              mutate(REGISTRY_ID = as.double(REGISTRY_ID)) %>% 
              select(REGISTRY_ID, LATITUDE83, LONGITUDE83), by='REGISTRY_ID')

subsetting to facilities that have valid location and within mainland US

num_NA <- sum(is.na(fac_merged$LATITUDE83))

# around 2000 out of ~24000 facilities have no location data i.e around 8.3%

# filtering out NA's in location columns
fac_merged <- fac_merged %>% 
  filter(!is.na(LATITUDE83), !STATE %in% c('AK', 'HI', 'PR'), LONGITUDE83 < 0)

converting to sf object

fac_sf <- st_as_sf(fac_merged,
                  coords = c("LONGITUDE83", "LATITUDE83"),
                  remove = F,
                  crs = 4326)

reading in air monitoring station dataset

monitor_data <- read_feather(file.path('/projects/caa-ml/raw_data/air_monitoring/aqs_monitors.feather')) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  group_by(latitude, longitude) %>% 
  mutate(count = n(),
         parameter_new = ifelse(count > 1, "Multiple", parameter_name),
         parameter_list = toString(parameter_name)) %>%
  distinct(latitude, longitude, parameter_new, .keep_all = TRUE)

# saving the condensed df
write_feather(monitor_data, file.path("/projects/caa-ml/raw_data/air_monitoring",
                                   "aqs_monitors_condensed.feather"))

#converting to sf object
monitor_sf <- st_as_sf(monitor_data,
                  coords = c("longitude", "latitude"),
                  remove = F,
                  crs = 4326)

pal <- colorFactor(palette = c('red', 'yellow', 'green', 'black', 'brown', 'blue',
                               'purple', 'pink') , monitor_sf$parameter_new)

plotting facilities and stations

# creating icon for facilities
triangle_green <- makeIcon(iconUrl = "https://www.freeiconspng.com/uploads/green-normal-triangle-png-8.png",
                             iconWidth = 15, iconHeight = 15)
leaflet() %>%
  addTiles() %>% 
  addMarkers(data = fac_sf, lng = ~LONGITUDE83, lat = ~LATITUDE83, 
             icon = triangle_green,
             clusterOptions = markerClusterOptions(),
             label = paste("Facility ID =", fac_sf$REGISTRY_ID,
                           "Type =", fac_sf$FAC_TYPE,
                           "City =", fac_sf$CITY,
                           "State =", fac_sf$STATE)) %>% 
  addCircles(data = monitor_sf,
             lat = ~latitude, lng = ~longitude,
             radius = 20000,
             color = ~pal(parameter_new),
             label = paste("Pollutant=", monitor_sf$parameter_list),
             stroke = FALSE, fillOpacity = 0.2, opacity = 0.2) %>% 
  addLegend('bottomleft', pal = pal, values = monitor_sf$parameter_new,
            title = 'List of Pollutants',
            
            opacity = 0.5)
